            {"q": "In which of the following reactions are the underlined species oxidized? I. 2Fe²⁺ → 2Fe³⁺ II. S²⁻ → S III. 2Mg → 2MgO IV. 2Al → 2Al³⁺", "opts": ["I-IV", "I-III", "I, III, IV", "IV only"], "ans": 1, "exp": "Oxidation = increase in oxidation state. Fe²⁺→Fe³⁺ (I), S²⁻→S (II), Mg→Mg²⁺ (III) are all oxidized. I-III are correct."},
            {"q": "Which of the following decreases left to right across period but increases down the group? I. Ionization energy II. Electron affinity III. Electronegativity IV. Atomic radius", "opts": ["I-IV", "I-III", "III-IV", "IV only"], "ans": 3, "exp": "Atomic radius DECREASES across a period and INCREASES down a group. Only atomic radius (IV) fits this pattern."},
            {"q": "A homologous series is one in which: I. All compounds have one general formula II. Successive members differ by CH₃ III. Physical properties differ only by carbon number IV. Members have same physical and chemical properties", "opts": ["I-IV", "I, III", "III-IV", "IV only"], "ans": 1, "exp": "A homologous series: shares one general formula (I), successive members differ by CH₂ (NOT CH₃), physical properties vary with carbon number (III). I and III are correct."},
            {"q": "Which is/are correct of the ammonia molecule? I. Tetrahedral shape II. Has a lone pair of electrons III. H-N-H bond angle is 180° IV. Non-polar molecule", "opts": ["I-IV", "I-III", "III-IV", "None of the above"], "ans": 3, "exp": "NH₃ has trigonal pyramidal shape (not tetrahedral), H-N-H angle is ~107° (not 180°), and it IS polar. Only II (lone pair) is correct — but no option matches, so 'None of the above'."},
            {"q": "What reactions occur at electrodes during electrolysis of concentrated NaCl solution? I. Oxidation at the anode II. Cl₂ evolved at the anode III. H₂ evolved at the cathode IV. O₂ evolved at the cathode", "opts": ["I-IV", "I-III", "I only", "IV only"], "ans": 1, "exp": "At anode: 2Cl⁻→Cl₂+2e⁻ (I and II correct). At cathode: 2H₂O+2e⁻→H₂+2OH⁻ (III correct). O₂ NOT evolved at cathode (IV wrong). So I-III."},
            {"q": "Which is correct of the gaseous state? I. Intermolecular spaces are very large II. Molecules move very fast III. Intermolecular forces are negligible IV. Intermolecular spaces can be compressed", "opts": ["I-IV", "I-III", "III-IV", "I, II, IV"], "ans": 0, "exp": "All four are correct for gases: very large intermolecular spaces (I), fast molecules (II), negligible forces (III), and gases are compressible (IV)."},
            {"q": "Which of these are isomers of butanol? I. 2-methyl-2-propanol II. Methoxy propanol III. 1-propanol", "opts": ["I only", "I and II", "II and III", "All of the above"], "ans": 0, "exp": "Butanol has formula C₄H₉OH. 2-methyl-2-propanol (tert-butanol) is C₄H₉OH — an isomer. 1-propanol is C₃H₇OH — not an isomer. So I only."},
            {"q": "Which of the following is NOT part of natural water? I. Rain water II. Water vapour III. Deionised water IV. Distilled water", "opts": ["III and IV", "III only", "II only", "I only"], "ans": 0, "exp": "Natural water includes rain water and water vapour. Deionised and distilled water are processed — not naturally occurring. So III and IV."},
