            {"q": "Which gas is insoluble in water and can be collected over water?", "opts": ["Ammonia", "Hydrogen chloride", "Oxygen", "Sulphur dioxide"], "ans": 2, "exp": "Oxygen is sparingly soluble and can be collected by displacement of water. Ammonia and HCl are highly soluble; SO₂ is moderately soluble."},
            {"q": "Which of the following has the highest ionization energy?", "opts": ["Sodium", "Neon", "Magnesium", "Aluminium"], "ans": 1, "exp": "Neon is a noble gas with a completely filled outer shell. It has the highest ionization energy due to its extreme stability."},
