            {"q": "When alkane reacts with halogen, what type of reaction does it undergo?", "opts": ["Addition", "Substitution", "Cracking", "Polymerization"], "ans": 1, "exp": "Alkanes undergo free radical substitution with halogens in UV light. The halogen atom substitutes a hydrogen atom."},
            {"q": "Which of the following is used in making aircraft?", "opts": ["Brass", "Bronze", "Duralumin", "Steel"], "ans": 2, "exp": "Duralumin is an aluminium alloy (Al+Cu+Mg+Mn) that is light but strong — ideal for aircraft construction."},
            {"q": "Which of the following is liquid at room temperature?", "opts": ["Mercury", "Bromine", "Sodium", "Gallium"], "ans": 0, "exp": "Mercury (Hg) and Bromine (Br₂) are both liquid at room temperature. Mercury is the standard answer as a liquid metal."},
