            {"q": "Which of the following is the correct IUPAC name for CH₃CH₂CHO?", "opts": ["Propanal", "Propanone", "Propanoic acid", "Propan-1-ol"], "ans": 0, "exp": "CHO at the end indicates an aldehyde. Three carbons = prop-. Propanal is CH₃CH₂CHO (propanal = propan-1-al)."},
