            {"q": "Which of the following solutions will have a pH less than 7?", "opts": ["NaCl", "Na₂CO₃", "CH₃COONa", "NH₄Cl"], "ans": 3, "exp": "NH₄Cl is a salt of a strong acid (HCl) and weak base (NH₃). It hydrolyzes to give an acidic solution (pH < 7)."},
