            {"q": "The unit of rate of reaction is:", "opts": ["Moldm³s¹", "Mol⁻¹dm³s", "Moldm⁻³s⁻¹", "Moldm³s⁻¹"], "ans": 2, "exp": "Rate = change in concentration / time = mol dm⁻³ / s = mol dm⁻³ s⁻¹."},
            {"q": "Which of the following is true about catalyst and equilibrium? I. Catalyst produces greater yield II. It has no effect on equilibrium III. It reduces concentration of reactants", "opts": ["I and II", "II", "III", "II and III"], "ans": 1, "exp": "A catalyst speeds up both forward and reverse reactions equally, reaching equilibrium faster but NOT changing position of equilibrium or yield. Only II is correct."},
