            {"q": "1 farad is equivalent to:", "opts": ["1 coulomb/volt", "1 volt/coulomb", "1 joule/coulomb", "1 ampere/sec"], "ans": 0, "exp": "Capacitance C = Q/V. Therefore 1 Farad = 1 Coulomb/Volt."},
            {"q": "Two bodies with masses M and 4M are moving with the same kinetic energy. The ratio of their velocities is:", "opts": ["2:1", "1:2", "1:4", "4:1"], "ans": 0, "exp": "KE = ½mv². For equal KE: ½Mv₁² = ½(4M)v₂² → v₁²/v₂² = 4 → v₁/v₂ = 2. Ratio v₁:v₂ = 2:1."},
            {"q": "A faulty thermometer has ice point -4°C and steam point 104°C, reads 32°C. The correct temperature is:", "opts": ["100°C", "0°C", "33.3°C", "89°C"], "ans": 2, "exp": "T_correct = (T_faulty - ice point)/(steam-ice) × 100 = (32-(-4))/(104-(-4)) × 100 = (36/108) × 100 = 33.3°C."},
