            {"q": "If angle of incidence on a plane mirror is 25° and the mirror is rotated by 15°, the angle the reflected ray is turned is:", "opts": ["10°", "30°", "40°", "20°"], "ans": 1, "exp": "When a mirror is rotated by angle θ, the reflected ray rotates by 2θ. Rotation = 15°, so reflected ray rotates by 30°."},
            {"q": "When sound travels from air to water: I. Velocity decreases II. Velocity increases III. Frequency remains constant IV. Frequency increases", "opts": ["I, II", "I only", "IV, then III", "II and III"], "ans": 3, "exp": "Sound moves faster in water (denser medium). Frequency is a property of the source and does not change. So II and III."},
            {"q": "A fixed mass of gas is heated at constant volume so that Celsius temperature is doubled. The pressure:", "opts": ["Is halved", "Is doubled", "Is more than doubled", "Increases but less than doubled"], "ans": 3, "exp": "Using Gay-Lussac's Law: P₁/T₁ = P₂/T₂ (absolute). Doubling Celsius doesn't double Kelvin temperature. Pressure increases but less than doubled."},
